Instead of allowing these deletions you REPOSTED all messages as soon as you came back online. I was forced to remove identical messages as often as 20 or 30 times. I would have deleted you from the membership at this point for spamming but a glitch prevented me from doing so. Then you tried to act the innocent and get the other founders on side. <br>
<br>
I eventually blew up at you and being the opportunistic little weasel you are you copied the page and sent a complaint to Yahoo. Big deal. I have sent countless complaints about flamers and spammers to Yahoo and know I'm not the only one to do so. They never reply in person. Only ever send autoreplies. So your sting was pointless. <br>
<br>
Remember that lie you posted to all your friends at EverythingSpace in which you claimed to have been in contact with Yahoo? Yes, the one where you told them Yahoo had said Project Orion club was hanging by a thread. It would be deleted soon. Got caught with your pants down there now didn't you. <br>
<br>
Cut out the amateur attempts at manipulation and the pathetic whining act. The only person fooled is yourself if you think anyone is buying it.  <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
